    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">1. Underestimating Sector Restrictions</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Vietnam has over 200 "conditional" business sectors with various restrictions—from complete prohibition
            of foreign investment to ownership caps to additional licensing requirements. Always verify your intended
            business activity with a qualified legal advisor before investing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">2. Insufficient Charter Capital</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            While there's no legal minimum for most sectors, authorities expect capital "sufficient for stated
            activities." Declaring too little charter capital raises red flags and may result in rejection. Under-
            capitalized companies also face operational challenges getting bank credit and supplier terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">3. Skipping International Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Public hospitals have limited quality for complex care. International hospitals charge $500-$1,500 per
            outpatient visit, $15,000-$50,000 for hospitalization. Without insurance, a serious illness can wipe
            out your investment. Always include evacuation coverage to Singapore/Bangkok.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">4. Late Capital Deposit</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Charter capital must be deposited within 90 days of ERC issuance. Late deposit triggers penalties and
            can jeopardize your investment license. Transfer funds promptly and retain bank confirmation documents
            for tax and visa purposes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">5. Ignoring Compliance Requirements</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Vietnamese companies face extensive reporting obligations—monthly tax declarations, quarterly social
            insurance, annual audits. Non-compliance results in fines and can affect visa renewal. Budget for
            ongoing accounting and compliance services ($200-$500/month minimum).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

